  "description": "Change of use of ground floor of No. 140 from doctors surgery (Use Class Ee) to residential (Use Class C3), part two storey, part single storey full width rear extension and replacement roof with addition of front dormers and rear gable dormer extensions to create additional habitable roofspace, to create 1 x studio, 4 x 1-bed and 2 x 2 bed flats with associated parking and amenity space, involving demolition of existing extensions and detached garage with external alterations, roof lights and boundary treatments",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "In the absence of details satisfactorily demonstrating that the loss of a community facility would not be prejudicial to the local community, the proposed development is contrary to Policy DC27 of the Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document.",
    "The proposed layout of the development would be inadequate resulting in substandard accommodation for future residents through lack of internal space. As a result, the development represents an overdevelopment of the site contrary to Policy DC61 of the Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document, the DCLG Technical Housing Standards and Policy D6 of the London Plan.",
    "The cumulative impact of the rear gable dormer extensions would, by reason of their excessive width, scale, bulk, mass and prominent location of the site, appear incongruous, dominant and visually intrusive in the streetscene and in the rear garden environment harmful to the character and appearance of the surrounding area contrary to Policy DC61 of the Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document.",
    "The proposed development would, by reason of a lack of private amenity space provision for the second floor apartments 3.01 and 3.02, be harmful to the amenity of future occupiers contrary to Policy DC61 of Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document, the Design for Living Residential Design Supplementary Planning Document and Policy D6 of the London Plan.",
    "The proposed first floor rear extension would, by reason of its depth, siting and position close to the boundaries of the site, be unneighbourly, appear overbearing and result in a significant loss of amenity to No. 136 Station Lane, including loss of light, contrary to Policy DC61 of the Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document and the Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to MiU Design Limited via email on 12th May 2021.",
